Field.Name: PartType
Field.Description: Name of the machine part.

Field.Name: Mounted
Field.Description: Flag stating if the part is currently mounted or not.

Field.Name: Traceable
Field.Description: Flag stating if the part is traceable (e.g. has an id or serial number).

Field.Name: PartId
Field.Description: Id or serial number of the part.

Field.Name: MachineReadable
Field.Description: Flag stating if the PartId is machine readable.

Field.Name: LastCalibrationDate
Field.Description: Date of the last calibration of this part if available.

Field.Name: JobId
Field.Description: The unique id given to the job by the client (MES)

Field.Name: RecipeId
Field.Description: The available recipes are stored on the TTD and are referenced by their id.

Field.Name: NumberOfTests
Field.Description: This array contains TestNumDataType structures that describe how many tests per procedures have to be performed.

Field.Name: SampleInfos
Field.Description: This array contains SampleInfoDataType structures that hold the information about the samples that have to be tested.

Field.Name: CarrierTypeId
Field.Description: Id to identify the creel geometry of the geometry of the fiber container.

Field.Name: CarrierId
Field.Description: Id of the fiber container or carrier/creel. For creels represents the number of the creel wagon.

Field.Name: AdditionalInfo
Field.Description: A set of key/value pairs to provide additional information for a job.

Field.Name: Scheduled
Field.Description: Indicates if a job was scheduled by a remote client(MES).

Field.Name: ModuleName
Field.Description: The name of the module.

Field.Name: ModuleType
Field.Description: The type of the module. E.g. hardware/software.

Field.Name: IsInstalled
Field.Description: Flag that indicates if the module is installed.

Field.Name: Version
Field.Description: Version of the soft-/hardware module.

Field.Name: RecipeId
Field.Description: RecipeId meta data describing this recipe.

Field.Name: RecipeContent
Field.Description: The content of this recipe as ByteString.

Field.Name: ContentEncoding
Field.Description: The encoding of the content. E.g. UTF-8 or ASCII

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: Human readable name for the recipe.

Field.Name: Id
Field.Description: System wide unique id for the file content. (E.g. Hash of file content is possible)

Field.Name: Type
Field.Description: The type of the textile testing device for which the recipe is applicable.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Description of the recipe.

Field.Name: Comment
Field.Description: Comment on the recipe.

Field.Name: ModifiedDate
Field.Description: The date of the last modification to the recipe file.

Field.Name: Version
Field.Description: Version of the recipe.

Field.Name: Validated
Field.Description: Flag that indicates if the recipe was successfully validated on the textile testing device. Null if the validation was not performed.

Field.Name: SampleId
Field.Description: The unique identifier of one sample.

Field.Name: TesterJobId
Field.Description: TTD internal id given to the tested set of samples(job)

Field.Name: TesterSampleResultId
Field.Description: Unique identifier created by the TTD for each sample result. Necessary additional to the SampleId if the sample is tested more than once.

Field.Name: ProductInstanceURI
Field.Description: Unique product instance uri of the TTD.

Field.Name: CanBeDeleted
Field.Description: Flag set by the client that indicates if the TTD may delete the result.

Field.Name: JobOrder
Field.Description: The metadata for the job containing parameters like linear density, RecipeId, NumberOfTests and SampleInfo.

Field.Name: SampleId
Field.Description: The unique identifier of a (physical) sample.

Field.Name: NominalLinearDensity
Field.Description: The nominal linear density of this sample in tex. It is used for calculating linear density related parameters.

Field.Name: MaterialDensity
Field.Description: The material density in g/cmÂ³. It is used for calculating some test results like diameter.

Field.Name: MaterialType
Field.Description: The material type information can be used to switch between material dependend handling of material or for reporting.

Field.Name: PositionOnCarrier
Field.Description: Position of the sample on the carrier. If there is no carrier an empty String should be provided.

Field.Name: ResultKey
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the measured property defined by the tester application.

Field.Name: ItemCount
Field.Description: Number of valid tests that were calculated in the statistics.

Field.Name: MeanValue
Field.Description: Mean value of the valid tests.

Field.Name: StandardDeviation
Field.Description: Standard-Deviation of the valid tets.

Field.Name: CoefficientOfVariation
Field.Description: Coefficient of variation of valid tests.

Field.Name: MinValue
Field.Description: The minimum value of the valid tests.

Field.Name: MaxValue
Field.Description: The maximum value of the valid tests.

Field.Name: ConfidenceInterval95
Field.Description: Confidence interval (95%) of the measurement.

Field.Name: UnitItemCount
Field.Description: Unit for the ItemCount.

Field.Name: UnitMeanValue
Field.Description: Unit for the MeanValue.

Field.Name: UnitStandardDeviation
Field.Description: Unit for the StandardDeviation.

Field.Name: UnitCoefficientOfVariation
Field.Description: Unit for the CoefficientOfVariation.

Field.Name: UnitMinValue
Field.Description: Unit for the MinValue.

Field.Name: UnitMaxValue
Field.Description: Unit for the MaxValue.

Field.Name: UnitConfidenceInterval
Field.Description: Unit for the ConfidenceInterval.

Field.Name: TestProcedureId
Field.Description: The name of the test procedure that should be executed.

Field.Name: NumberOfTests
Field.Description: The number of tests that have to be performed with this test procedure on one sample.

Field.Name: TestProcedureId
Field.Description: The available test procedures are stored on the testing device and referenced by name (TestProcedureId).

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Description of the test procedure.

Field.Name: ProcedureReferences
Field.Description: An array of references to standards.

Field.Name: IsProcedureLicensed
Field.Description: Flag to define the availability on the server.

UAObjectType.Description: Provides information of a complete or partial result.

uax:Description.uax:Text: System-wide unique identifier for the result.

With this argument the client can give a hint to the server how long it will need access to the result data. A value > 0 indicates an estimated maximum time for processing the data in milliseconds. A value = 0 indicates that the client will not need anything besides the data returned by the method call. A value < 0 indicates that the client cannot give an estimate. The client cannot rely on the data being available during the indicated time period. The argument is merely a hint allowing the server to optimize its resource management.

The server shall return to each client requesting result data a system-wide unique handle identifying the result set / client combination. This handle should be used by the client to indicate to the server that the result data is no longer needed, allowing the server to optimize its resource handling. If the instance of ResultManagementType does not support the ReleaseResultHandle Method, the resultHandle should always be set to 0. If the error is set to a value other than 0, the resultHandle may be set to 0.
The result including metadata. May be set to Null, if error is set to a value other than 0.

Options how to generate the file, including the resultId of the result the file belongs to.
NodeId of the temporary file.
The FileHandle of the opened TransferFile. The FileHandle can be used to access the TransferFile methods Read and Close.

If the creation of the file is completed asynchronously, the parameter returns the NodeId of the corresponding FileTransferStateMachineType Object. If the creation of the file is already completed, the parameter is null. If a FileTransferStateMachineType object NodeId is returned, the Read Method of the file fails until the TransferState changed to ReadTransfer.
